\f1\b0\fs44 \cf0 Homemade Chicken Stock:\
3 (5-pound) chickens\
3 large {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/onion/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 onions}}, unpeeled and quartered\
6 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/carrot/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 carrots}}, unpeeled and halved\
4 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/celery/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 celery}} stalks with leaves, cut in thirds\
4 parsnips, unpeeled and cut in half (optional)\
20 sprigs fresh {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/parsley/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 flat-leaf parsley}}\
15 sprigs fresh thyme\
20 sprigs fresh dill\
1 head {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/garlic/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 garlic}}, unpeeled and cut in 1/2 crosswise\
2 tablespoons kosher salt\
2 teaspoons whole black peppercorns\
Place the chickens, onions, carrots, celery, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/parsnip/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 parsnips}}, parsley, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/thyme/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 thyme}}, dill, garlic, salt, and peppercorns in a 16 to 20-quart stockpot with 7 quarts of water and bring to a boil. Skim the surface as needed. Simmer uncovered for 4 hours. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/strain/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Strain}} the entire contents of the pot through a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/colander/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 colander}}, discarding the chicken and vegetables, and chill. Discard the hardened fat, and then pack the broth in quart containers.\
Yield: 6 quarts\
